# **Core Principles (Use in Every Filing)**

- Childâ€‘First Anchor. Tie each request to safety, stability, health, and educational continuity.
- Specifics > Adjectives. Replace character labels with dated facts, short quotes, and documents.
- Offer the Middle. Always include a reasonable alternative and a collaboration step.
- Own Small Misses. Briefly acknowledge deviations, show notice, and explain a childâ€‘centered rationale.
- Document, Donâ€™t Diagnose. Describe behavior and impact on the child; avoid amateur psychology.
- Deâ€‘escalation. Propose communication boundaries/tools (OurFamilyWizard, TalkingParents, limited channels).
- Filing Header Helper (1â€‘sentence anchor to place up front):
- â€œThis request is limited to measures that stabilize the childâ€™s schooling, therapy, and transitions. No relief is sought that would reduce the other parentâ€™s meaningful contact.â€
